                                                                                <due></due>
                            <votes>1</votes>
                                    <watches>8</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="488645" author="laisiyao" created="Mon, 23 Feb 2026 13:11:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;MGS provides below services:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;generate Lustre system configurations upon target register&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;provide configurations to nodes in the system, including both servers and clients&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;notify configuration changes to other nodes&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;notify server restarts (imperative recovery) to shorten timeout&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;There should be only one MGS (MGS0) to generate configurations, otherwise it will cause brain split. As a result, MGS0 acts the same as current MGS, and the MGS replicas keep the configurations in sync with MGS0, and only need to provide configurations to clients, and they should notify clients when configuration changes or server restarts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
